Key Match Events: Alec Bohm's RBI single in the 10th inning lifted the Phillies past the Mets 5-4.
J.T. Realmuto hit a three-run homer in the 6th inning.
Francisco Lindor and Brett Baty each hit solo home runs for the Mets in the 8th and 9th innings respectively.
Miscellaneous Highlights: The game was held at Citizens Bank Park with an attendance of 38,795.
The game lasted 3 hours and 9 minutes.
